    "body": "Unless the nuke hits water most things in the water in real life will be fine, if it hits the water then a pressure wave will pretty much crunch everything within range. The reason they are fine if it doesn't hit the water is the pressure wave will glide over the water the same for trenches which you can see in some old atomic test videos.\n"
